cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.ST

This paper discusses the use of loss functions in machine learning, specifically in binary classification problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the Kullback-Leibler divergence, which is a concept in information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. The use of loss functions is also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), and statistics (cs.ST), making these sub-categories also possible.
